Task 5-A09: Logging & Alerting Failures:
              Logging & Alerting Failures happen when an application does not properly record or monitor important security
              events. Without proper logs, it becomes very difficult to detect attacks, investigate incidents, or prove what actions
              were performed by a user.
              In practice, this includes missing login records, unclear error messages, no alerts for suspicious activity (like
               brute-force attacks), short log storage, or logs that attackers can modify. During an investigation, logs are
              crucial to understand what happened—if key information is missing, tracing the attack becomes extremely difficult
              or even impossible.

